In regards to archery,
     One of the types of shoots I have seen around here
(Southern Ansteorra) is the money pouch shoot. A cloth 
bag is filled with coins and suspended from a tripod. 
The object is to hit the bag and tear it. Any
coins which you dislodge are yours. This necessitates 
some alterations to the typical shooting line. The time
I saw it everyone shot in order going down the line so
it was known who had gotten the hit. When money fell
all shooting was stopped and the archer went up to 
collect his booty. I saw one bag (fairly thick) withstand
20 or so hits before it completely tore open but did allow 
a few earlier hits to dislodge some coins through tears
and such. The shooters got closer after every four or so 
arrows and there was a large effort to shoot quickly
one after the other to kepp the round from taking 
forever. This was run by Lord Leon Dunne of Bryn Gwlad
and Jusseric Allison of Bjornsborg. Just knowing them
I would assume this a documentably period shoot.
