>All of this
>was using the mundane fencing standard of 350 gram touches.  In Ansteorra,
>the only Kingdom I've lived in that allowed fencing, the standard SCA
>touch was expected to be 500 grams, using normal fencing blades, WHICH
>ARE *NOT* MADE FOR THAT LEVEL OF STRESS!

Eh?  Under USFA rules a valid touch is 500g for foil, 750g for epee.

And that's a very light touch!  I'd say your "average" touch is about
1 kg, maybe 1500 g for epee, and even that is no problem at all as far
as broken blades are concerned.  Masks are required to withstand a
12 kg punch test (the punch tip is about the size of a pencil point and
the mesh must be strong enough not to spread apart under that pressure.

There are some very heavy-handed fencers out there.  When I direct,
I have no qualms about giving warnings for brutal hits....there is
NEVER any reason to hit that hard, even in a fleche attack.

