there; it sounds like just the kind of way I'd like to see Crowns held.

The major problem, it seems to me, is inertia. We have twenty years of
tradition here, and even the most liberal people are loathe to drop that
in favor of new ways, even if those new ways are "better". It simply
isn't clear whether the mechanisms of the Society are capable to making
changes that are this *radical*. This seems to be why many of the
splinter groups get formed: someone has a good idea that doesn't conform
to the SCA's Way Of Doing Things, and can't get the Society to change,
so they go off and do things their own way.

