I speak as a Master-at-Arms of the East.  I have had almost no contact
with other Kingdoms, and am at present relatively inactive on the Touring
Pro Circuit.  "Back when i was good" :-) i had a reputation for skill and
speed but not power, and have always been respected for my Wimpy Eastern --
uh, i mean Chivalrous -- calibration level, both giving and taking.  :-)

The main problem as i see it is that there is no effective feedback to
fighters except in extreme cases.  Most of this is caused by sheer numbers;
there are a great number of fighters and relatively few members of the
Chivalry.  If some of the Chivalry are also problems (which point i grant
for the sake of argument only) then things become that much worse.

What the fighters in general, and the Chivalry in particular, need is a
Rhino-Hotline.  Whenever you think you've been pounded to hamburger
unnecessarily, or feel that your best imitation of a 16-ton weight really
*should* have carried the day, you call the RH and detail the incident.
The RH keeps records, and whenever anyone wants to check on his or her
reputation, he or she just calls the RH and checks the file.

There are, of course, details to be worked out and problems to avoid, but
the basic concept -- written complaints -- doesn't exist at the moment.
I can't imagine anyone taking up the thankless task of keeping track of
everything, but no doubt it could be parlayed into a position of authority
in the Kingdom, so maybe someone will.

