careful that your loaner gear is safe.  I think velcro tabs and several
individual pieces of padding will make the helm safe, the armor is
still in the design stages. Ideas anyone?

	As for fencing...  I'm a moderately proficient (mundane) fencer.
I've never been injured (except for some bloodied knuckles when a new
fencer tried to sabre fence with a foil  :-)  though I have had a number 
blades break on me over the years... it is scary.  I have had a friend
stabbed (though not seriously, only 1/2 inch penetration.)  All of this
was using the mundane fencing standard of 350 gram touches.  In Ansteorra,
the only Kingdom I've lived in that allowed fencing, the standard SCA
touch was expected to be 500 grams, using normal fencing blades, WHICH
ARE *NOT* MADE FOR THAT LEVEL OF STRESS!  Is it any wonder that there
was a shorter blade-lifetime?   And unlike broken rattan, broken 
foils are potentially lethal.  

