laundry.  That was nieve.  This is a perfect forum to deal with problems.
Yet, I, who is facing some fairly monsterous political dung-heaps, feels
that this is still TOO PUBLIC to air some of the dirty laundry that I am
sitting on.  Maybe it is just too ripe, or this list is simply too public.
We have over 100 sites receiving this mail... and much of it is redistributed.

Anything over these networks is public knowledge.  Anyone can request to be 
part of this list.  *IT* is public knowledge.  Anything written down is in the
public domain.  Should we silence every "ripe" topic?  No, I think if a person
wants to find out about the SCA, they should know about our good and our bad.

-----------------------

Now lets look at some realities.  SCA@AI.AI.MIT.EDU must move to its sister
machine MC because we are overtaxing that system.  We have over 100 sites
being mailed to at this time and our receiving requests each day for additional 
subscriptions.  Given the traffic of mail each day, we will overtax MC as well,
but we will not anger anybody, to much, doing it (MC is a machine dedicated to
mail and mailing lists).  The moderator, me, is overworked and is spending at 
least three hours a day maintaining the list... more on weekends.  (With work,
I can make this process more efficient.)  That is in addition to his normal 
workload.

SCA@AI is growing, and growing too fast.  In order to deal with the system over-
load those users who want, will tolerate, or can be convinced will receive a 
digested version of the mailings. Some users will receive sca@ai via alt.sca
newsgroup.  The rest will receive it in the same form as it is now.  

----------------------

If we do not support alt.sca, I will have to support the users who wish to
participate in this forum who would do so through alt.sca.  In time, any 
host site will find problems with the traffic and INSIST on digesting this
list.  MANY of you do not want to digest it.  If we do not allow some method
to relieve the "pressure" of its distribution... then its future is as a 
digest.


Your in service to the society,

