About four years ago, Lord Nis von den Eichenberger came up with a good
idea on this topic--the creation of a local minor office, under the
Knight Marshalate, known as the Iron Key.  It stores, maintains, loans
and keeps track of extra armor.  We started with the unclaimed Lost and
Found armor from Pennsic XIII, plus a number of local contributions.
The Iron Key currently can field about three complete sets of armor,
many and varied weapons (illegal unclaimed weapons are dismantled and
used to make legal ones), extra helms, gauntlets, gorgets and various
other small pieces.  

Additionally, for the past few years the Iron Key has collected the
Lost and Found armor from Pennsic and sent notices to that effect to 
the Kingdom newsletters.  People who have lost armor and weapons at
Pennsic have until Twelfth Night to notify the Iron Key, see if they
have the piece in question (sometimes we don't), and arrange for its
return.  After Twelfth Night, anything left reverts to the BMDL; we
give away some of it and refurbish other pieces.

Most of our nicer pieces are from private contributions.  Nice things
left at Pennsic are rarely left unclaimed.  Since this is the case, I
think that the Iron Key idea would work in other groups as well.  The
main requirements are dry storage space and the ability to handle some
recordkeeping.  Our current officeholders are good at fixing stuff, as
well, but this could be done by outside volunteers.

We have also funded the purchase of extra helms for Iron Key from
general Baronial funds.

Does anybody else out there have a similar system in place?

--Marian Greenleaf

