Greetings!

I note that Lord Tofi has arranged an automatic interface between
alt.sca & our mailing list.  This is an interesting arrangement, very
convenient for those of us who have been receiving 30-40 letters per
day on the mailing list, and rather a neat setup, all things
considered.  However, this connection effects a serious change in the
nature of the mailing list, one which we may want to consider
carefully.

Alt.sca is a public newsgroup, distributed all over the world.  It can
be read by anyone, and anyone can post to it.  It cannot be restricted
in any way.  The mailing list is a private discussion forum for SCA
members only.  We can discuss anything we want, air our dirty laundry,
without any worry about bad publicity or other ill effects.  Consider,
for example, the potential effect of the recent discussions of
paganism in the Society.  In light of the recent unfortunate incidents
of one idiot giving the SCA lots of loud bad press, I think we have a
duty to be very careful about how we distribute our discussions, or a
duty to restrict our topics.  Either solution is unpleasant, but I
think we would be foolish to discount the problems that might arise
from the current setup.  

Therefore, I have asked Lord Tofi to temporarily dismantle his
interface, and I ask all of you to think about these matters and
express your opinions.  I would like to see a clear consensus one way
or the other before we commit ourselves.

Yours in service to the Society,

	Arval Benicoeur.


