Unto Dafydd Bleiddan, and unto all others interested, 
From Arval Benicoeur, Brigantia Principal Herald, Greetings! 

My lord, you have come to the right place.  I'm from the East, but I
can give you a few pointers.  

First of all, you should contact heralds in your area to introduce
yourself, find out what regular meetings are going on, find out what
sorts of interesting books are available to borrow & read, and so on.
A good way to do this is to walk up to the list herald at any fighting
event and offer to help herald the lists.  Don't worry if you've never
done it before: you'll get a few quick pointers, make a few
unimportant mistakes, and catch on to the idea by the time the
afternoon is over.  And you'll have made a good friend.

You should try to contact Master Allyn o Dubhdha, in Storvik, who
just finished a term as Atlantia's Principal Herald, and now has lots
of time on his hands for teaching.  He would love to hear from someone
interested in learning, and is a fine teacher.  He also has a library
of heraldic texts I would happily kill to own.  If you have
transportation, you can easily drop by his place from time to time to
talk heraldry...I believe he holds regular heraldic research meetings.

On your own, you can get hold of some basic books & read up on
heraldry.  A few good ones are:

Shield & Crest, by Julian Franklyn

A Complete Guide to Heraldry, by A.C. Fox-Davies

An Encyclopedia of Heraldry, by A.C. Fox-Davies

These three books are basic introductions to mundane (English)
heraldry, and are good ways to learn basic things like colors,
charges, blazoning, and the like.  The first one on the list is my
favorite, because it is readable & contains 400+ pictures, some in
color, and each one is blazoned.  Unfortunately, it is often difficult
to find.  Check the university library.

For material on SCA heraldry, a good start is Compleat Anachronist
#22, Heraldry, by myself and Marten Broeker.  It discusses how to
design armory, and assumes a familiarity with mundane heraldic
terminology.  It is available from the Society Stock Clerk for $2.00.

Have fun & keep in touch.  Your servant,

		Arval Brigantia.


