Before any of you go out and buy this product, I would like to pass on
a review from Master Bruce Draconarius, Crescent Principal Herald of
Caid.  Not in his words, exactly, but the gist of it is that the
product is not really worth the purchase price.  It provides a library
of heraldic charges, many of which are of very poor quality
considering the power of the machine being used.  Most of the rest
seem to have been scanned straight out of Fox-Davies.  In addition,
the package contains some discussion & description of the use of
heraldry in general.  Most of this discussion is ENTIRELY
inappropriate in the context of the SCA, and much of it would be badly
misleading to the average SCAdian.  The product is aimed at the
genealogical crowd, the same people who respond to "Let Us Tell you
YOUR coat of arms" adds in magazines.  It does not attempt to discuss
period armory, and offers some rather poor advice.

In short, you could probably accomplish as much of SCA value with a
reducing phtotcopier & a pair of scissors.  

Note: I have not seen this package myself, but I have seen the review.
I would love to see the program...Can someone bring it to the Pennsic
War this year, or even better, to the Knowne World Heraldic Symposium in
Calontir this June?

