It is a REAL BAD IDEA to digest the SCA mailing list.  The new
newsgroup/mailinglist gateway won't cope well at all.  If the mailing
list is digiestified, then the gateway code has no way of telling
whether or not a message has allready been posted.  The result is that
a message is posted to alt.sca.  The gateway here at OSU sends it to
sca@ai.ai.mit.edu, where it is included in a digest.  When the digest
is sent out, the gateway code thinks that it is a new message, and
posts it to alt.sca, REPOSTING the original message.  Generally, a bad
idea all around.

So _please_ don't do this; a whole bunch of things will have to be set
up to cope with it properly...

