Subject: Politics in the SCA

Is there too much politicking in the Society? Sure -- any group of
this size is subject to the basic human love of power trips. More than
that, though, is the fact that it's simply easy for something to turn
into politics. An offhand comment that offends someone, an attempt to
start a friendly rivalry; these things and others can easily become
"politics" if we're not careful.

Really, the only way to deal with this is to refuse to participate in
the politics. We're all guilty of politicking, at least indirectly,
but we can work to lessen the burden. Before you take offense, try to
look at the other lord's (or lady's) point of view. If you are running
for a post, really try to look, objectively, at whether you would be
as good as the other person who wants it. And try to turn the other
cheek, no matter how much it burns the ego to do so. Only if we all
*try* to make things better can things actually *get* better. Politics
will always be with us, but we can make them less painful.

						-- Justin du Coeur

