I couldn't agree with you more.  One of the recent delightful
submissions which came through my office was the name change of "Alice
Gardener", spelled thus.  On the form, where it asks "Would you like
us to change the spelling of your name to get the meaning you want?",
Mistress Alys had written "Sure, go ahead.  I mean to vary the
spelling anyway."  And she does...

Spelling variation is a period phenomenon.  The use of different
nicknames or bynames at different times is, too, and the College of
Arms encourages gentles to so use their names in the period manner.
What I find objectionable is when someone submits a name, has it
returned as inappropriate for SCA use, and registers something else
"to placate the heralds", but goes right ahead using the name which he
was told would offend other members of the Society.  That is simply
rude, and it happens much too often.

