Among other points presented at Curia in favor of the underage fighter
ban was from Lord Friedrich av Knusslig Hamn.  Friedrich is mundanely
a school teacher.  In New York, if he sees a child who appears to have
been abused, and does not report it, then he can lose his teaching
certification.  This does NOT just apply to his students; it is a
general rule.

Recent court decisions make it very clear that allowing minor to
participate in combat is courting disaster: in most states, ANYONE can
file suit on behalf of an injured minor, and the parent's waiver is
irrelevent.  Parental permission does not exist in Pennsylvania:
temporary guardianship is not recognized by PA state courts.  If a
minor is injured, he may sue years later on his own behalf.  One such
suit could easily destroy the SCA.  

In the final analysis, it just isn't worth the risk.  Everyone agrees
that it is unfortunate that many valuable SCAdians suffer from this
rule, and no one likes the paperwork & hassle, but there just isn't
anything we can do about it.  We don't make the rules; the courts do.


