	Well, no doubt some of the more experianced gentles of the
Middle will answer, but I can offer some insight.

	As an intro, I started in Ansteora, but was not able to attend
many events due to my mundane job.  So I'm vague about the Ansteoran 
customs in a lot of areas.  But when I moved to the Middle I noticed
a few things.

	In both Kingdoms it is acceptable to where weapons to court.
The Merridian events I've attended had the same ease.  However,
before approaching the Crown one is to remove said weapons, as only
a very few are permitted in the Royal Presence with arms.  When    
someone approaches the Crown with weapons the King's Champion interposes
his/herself and begins to draw steel.  On at least one occation the
Crown has interceded and granted the privledge of carrying arms, in the
others I have seen the Champion remained in position until the offender
removed the weapon(s) or the audience was over.

	There does seem to ne a custom in the Middle of bowing to vacant
thrones, but it is not one that is rigidly obeyed.  It may be a way to
tell who's been around a while.      

	Face thrusts are verboten in the Middle.  Speaking as an Ansteoran,
these people take thier blows too damn hard!  There is a real worry of 
neck injurys due to face thrusts, particularly from pole arms, that
has led to this ban.  In Ansteora (when last I fought there) and in Merridies
face thrusts are legal.  (Which leads to the interesting question: do you
take a face thrust from a foriegner?  I do, as I'm on the border an fight
in Merridies frequently.  If the Marshal doesn't intervien (as one should
if it was illegal) then I'll take the blow.  Others are of different mind.)

	Allowing face thrusts does have one advantage: in makes pass and 
bridge battles a lot shorter!  

	I was reading the West's armor guidelines last night.  I've heard
that the West takes its blows hard, and judging from the rules I saw in
the Page this is true.  Would those of you that have your Kingdom's
Heavy Weapons rules and guidelines online mail me a copy?  I'd be interested
in seeing the differences.

	The West appears to allow 'killing from behind', something that 
all of the Kingdom's I've fought in have banned. (Fouling if someone
does not acknowledge your presence is legal, but striking is not.)  
Ansteora flirted with lower leg blows (shins) but appears to have 
banned them, something that most other kingdoms have consistantly 
outlawed.

	One custom that the Middle has that still bothers me is that the
crown list is open to all the Chivalry, and any others by invitation only.
In the other kingdom's that I have seen, the list is open to any who can
show membership, with a few qualifications (In Ansteora you had to have
served as a local officer for some period of time, and at the Crown
Tourney the Crown assembled the Chivalry and asked if any would speak for
the non-belted fighters in the list.  This last seemed a formality at
the crown I was able to attend, are there any Ansteoran's on the list who
can tell me if this has ever prevented someone from the fighting for crown?)
I'm told that the Middle's custom is to prevent a pure sword-jock from
winning crown and then not being able to do the work, or else making a
shambles of the Kingdom.  It still seems a little harsh to me.  Politics
being what they are, I worry that someone might be excluded, though 
this could certainly come from ignorance as well as malice.

	I fear this is too long already, so I'll close now with one more
thing.  My last two postings to the list seemed to be doubled.  I'm
sorry for this, I'm trying to trace the problem.

