from Arval Benicoeur, Brigantia Herald, and (St. Pyr help me!) War
Herald.

In the upcoming months, many events in and around the East will be
needing heavy heraldic turnout.  To wit:

Crown Tourney, An Dubhaigeainn, 21 May
War of the Roses, Concordia, Labor Day Weekend
Pennsic War, anyone who don't know is comatose

I will probably not be at War of the Roses, so I would like to request
of all Eastern heralds that you particularly try to ge there & help
out.  There should be a large consulting table, and they will need
major heraldic work for crying the camp.  think of as good practice
for...


The War.  Yes.  Well.  I would like to request that anyone who is
confident of his voice (no sexism, just grammatical convention) please
try to show up at Herald's Point to cry the camp once or twice during
the week.  Over the course of the week, I figure we need a total of
about 400 voices, which really isn't too much considering there will
be about 5000 people present.  We will have sign-up sheets, or you can
just drop by.  In addition, if you have a herald's tabard you can loan
us for the duration, we would deeply appreciate it.  For warranted
heralds: I expect every herald present at the War to stop by & meet
Badger Herald & me, and to cry the camp or otherwise contribute to the
general heraldic effort AT LEAST twice during the week.  That is what
you are being paid for.  And besides, we really really need you.  

