Subject: SCA DISTRIBUTION OUT OF SCA@AI.AI.MIT.EDU

SCA DISTRIBUTION is now an unmoderated SIG on the ARPA net.  Redistribution
is now automated out of AI.AI.MIT.EDU.  To post information to SCAnet 
participants just send mail to:

SCA@AI.AI.MIT.EDU

The purpose, as I have stated earlier, is to encourage communication,
especially to exchange ideas and research, within the SCA community from
coast to coast (and across the ocean, we hope).  Presently, information 
is passed more by hearsay than by fact.  Corporate publications can 
assist with overall informational dissemination, but they cannot explain what
is going on with rapier combat in the East kingdom as well as an East 
Kingdom fencer.  Nor, can they provide the instant feedback that networks
provide.  Hopefully, this will become an area and forum for controversial
thought as well as timely information.

Let us help it grow.  Please inform fellow SCAdians and have them contact the 
moderator at:

SCA-REQUEST@AI.AI.MIT.EDU

The moderator is Danulf Donaldson, aka: Dana Groff.

Please send node information in ARPA format and include the following 
information, if possible:

1) society name:
2) mundane name:
3) kingdom, group (and/or mundane location):
4) titles:
5) interests (brief):
6) do you want to be on the mailing list (y/n):
7) do you want to allow your node_address and information to be passed 
   onto other SCAdians (members of this list) (y/n):
8) node address (ARPA preferred):

I do not have this much information on many of you... so, please help me update
my information.  POINT 7 is important... your privacy is a concern.  I may 
one day wish to distribute my information, if you DO NOT WISH to have other
members of this mailing_list know of your address, then I will gladly keep it
quiet.  There are others who may wish to have people write to them directly,
but do not want to partake in any mailing lists, for this I have added point
6.

You may want to post an introduction to the conference as well.  The above
information should be sent to SCA-REQUEST.  It will not be redistributed to 
the conference.  If you wish to announce your existance and introduce yourself,
PLEASE DO... send that to the conference address at SCA@AI.AI.MIT.EDU.

USAGE NOTES:

Mail is redestributed as if you sent to each member on the list.  
SCA@AI.AI.MIT.EDU is not in the "from" field, so just replying to a note will
NOT send that note to the many members of the conference.  Further, if there
is ever networking trouble, YOU will receive the errors, not the moderator.
If you receive "failed mail" messages, please forward them to SCA-REQUEST.

PLEASE FEEL FREE TO DISTRIBUTE THIS LETTER

In service to the society,

Lord Danulf Donaldson, aka Dana Groff

